paper_abstract: We exhibit finite injury constructions of a high Sigma(2)(0) enumeration degree incomparable with all intermediate delta(2)(0) enumeration degrees, as also of both an upwards properly Sigma(2)(0) high and a low non-cuppable Sigma(0)(2) enumeration degree.We also outline how to apply the same methods to prove that, for every Sigma(2)(0) enumeration degree b there exists a non-cuppable degree a such that b' a' and a" b", thus showing that there exist non-cuppable Sigma(2)(0) enumeration degrees at every possible level of the high/low jump hierarchy.
paper_title: Non-cuppable enumeration degrees via finite injury
